👉 Can you do in-place?
Yes—in-place means modifying the input data structure without using extra space proportional to input size. Instead of creating a new array/string, the operation is done directly on the original one (usually using O(1) extra space).

👉 Can you handle Unicode?
Yes—handling Unicode means the solution correctly processes characters beyond basic ASCII (e.g., emojis, accented letters, non-Latin scripts). In practice, this may require:

Using proper string handling (like UTF-8/UTF-16 awareness)
Avoiding assumptions like “1 character = 1 byte”
